<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-1991] Groovyc: Pass specified classpath to Javac on Joint Compilation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1991</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When starting the groovyc compiler in the new Joint Compilation mode then the specified classpath is only used by the groovyc compiler, not by the Javac compiler.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In almost all cases these two compilers need the same classpath. But right now it&apos;s necessary to pass the same classpath a second time as a jointCompilationOption &quot;-Jclasspath=...&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
It would be great when this duplicate could get removed and the 2 compilers use the same classpath by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Linux (Ubuntu 7.04), Groovy 1.1 beta2</environment>
